{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#3348: Deriving child vNode props inside render function can be broken by static template optimization.",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:27:57.684845+00:00",
  "text": "Deriving child vNode props inside render function can be broken by static template optimization.\n\n### Version\r\n3.0.7\r\n\r\n### Reproduction link\r\n[https://codesandbox.io/s/strange-tree-1z4i0?file=/src/App.vue:0-2038](https://codesandbox.io/s/strange-tree-1z4i0?file=/src/App.vue:0-2038)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/18677354/109772095-8ff2d100-7c38-11eb-82ac-b808036d5c72.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\nFollow the link.\r\nI mean to derive some prop before its children do the first rendering. However it won't re-render in a template context.\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\nRe-render should work.\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\nDoesn't happening.\r\n\r\n<!-- generated by vue-issues. DO NOT REMOVE -->",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":lady_beetle:  bug",
    "scope: slots"
  ],
